hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: What do you do for a living? bentoz Summers’ recent comment, “Suppose then that the short term real interest rate that was consistent with full employment had fallen to negative two or negative three percent….” The idea that it would take negative interest to achieve full unemployment, combined with the comparison to Japan during the 1990s, suggests that what we are succeeding in doing today is fighting off deflation — but not much else.
